This paper deals with the problem of learning product embeddings for an e-commerce platform, which involves multiple data sources such as catalog text data, clickstream session data, and product images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with search, recommendation, and personalization systems. The paper also uses various machine learning techniques such as denoising auto-encoders, Bayesian personalized ranking, and Siamese neural network architecture, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
